INSERT IGNORE INTO `job` VALUES('Senior Quality Auditor', 'Not Specified', 'Not specified ', 'Not Specified', '0', 'Job SummaryThe Senior Quality Auditor is a senior member of the corporate Quality team . He supports the development and enforcement of corporate quality policies, procedures, tools and templates across K&A in coordination with regional and local quality teams. He participates in setting quality certification targets across K&A\'s offices and jointly works with regional and local teams for the development and implementation of action plans to achieve these certification targets. The jobholder develops quality audit plans across the organization, and tracks the execution of quality audits across K&A offices as per the audit plans to ensure the corporate-wide compliance with quality policies, procedures, tools and templates. He conducts QA activities on design deliverables prepared in the Lebanon design center to ensure the adherence of engineering design works to the organization\'s quality standards. The jobholder supports the delivery of quality training and awareness sessions across the organization in coordination with regional teams to promote an overarching quality culture.Key Responsibilities Support the development of corporate quality policies and procedures and provide guidelines for quality procedures in design Departments, Regions and Geographies Maintain the corporate Quality Management System (QMS) and investigate and recommend changes to the QMS, as needed Support the Director / Senior Manager - Quality with the definition of quality certification targets (e.g. ISO 9001) for all K&A offices Develop action plans for the implementation of quality certification targets across K&A offices, in coordination with regional / local Quality Units Conduct quality assurance activities on design deliverables developed in the Lebanon design center and check compliance of design deliverables to K&A\'s quality policies, procedures and standards Develop t